study_title: COVID-19-BWNW: A large-scale database of T-cell receptor beta (TCRb) sequences and binding associations from natural and synthetic exposure to SARS-CoV-2.
study_description: We describe the establishment and current content of the ImmuneCODE™ database, which includes hundreds of millions of T-cell Receptor (TCR) sequences from over 1,400 subjects exposed to or infected with the SARSCoV-2 virus, as well as over 135,000 high-confidence SARS-CoV-2-specific TCRs.
lab_address: 1551 Eastlake Ave E, Seattle, WA, US
sample_type: Whole blood samples were collected in K2EDTA tubes based on each institution’s protocol and supervised by their respective Institutional Review Board. Samples were stored at the institution and sent to Adaptive as frozen whole blood, isolated PBMC or DNA extracted from either sample type.
ab_symptoms: Fever;Nausea;Vomiting;Difficulty breathing;Fatigue;Shortness of breath;Loss of smell;Blood clots
library_generation_protocol: Immunosequencing of the CDR3 regions of human TCRβ chains was performed using the immunoSEQ Assay. Extracted genomic DNA was amplified in a bias-controlled multiplex PCR, followed by high-throughput sequencing. The Human-TCRB-PD4bx primer set was used.
software_versions: immunoSEQ Assay v4 (Adaptive Biotechnologies, Seattle, WA)
data_processing_protocols: TCRb analysis via the immunoSEQ Assay (Adaptive Biotechnologies, Seattle, WA). Sequences were collapsed and filtered in order to identify and quantitate the absolute abundance of each unique TCRβ CDR3 region for further analysis.
grants: Supported by Dept. of Health and Human Services, Office of the Assistant Secretary for Preparedness and Response, Biomedical Advanced Research and Development Authority, under Contract No. HHSO100201600031C, by the Division of Intramural Research, National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases, National Institutes of Health, by Regione Lombardia, Italy, and by CRIS foundation.
biomaterial_provider: Bloodworks Northwest - Whole blood samples from convalescent patients collected at Bloodworks Northwest (Seattle, WA)
